description:
value as specified by level (minTypmax) of the quotient of a wideband amplifier of: 1) the amplitude of the frequency component arising by the superposition of two input signals with specified amplitude and frequency (or channel) measured at a specified frequency (or channel), and 2) the amplitude of one of two original frequencies at specified supply voltage, temperature and temperature type.
Measuring method:| V_p = V_o,   f_p = f_1   (channel p);| V_q = V_o,   f_q = f_2   (channel q).| 2nd-order beat measured at (f_1 + f_2).
